-MY28bbkpwIwOtW3jo2W.text: Incident reported at 6242 Lee Ave N.

-MY28bh3HuwSjYBFS6lw.text: Citizen user video shows a group gathered in the area.

-MY2GReqCAq5iDyGdZnR.text: According to a tweet from the Minnesota Department of Public Safety Bureau of Criminal Apprehension, BCA agents and crime scene personnel are en route to an officer involved shooting incident in Brooklyn Center.

nib.text:
A group has gathered at 63rd Avenue North and Lee Avenue North in Brooklyn Center at the scene of a shooting involving police.

According to [Star Tribune](https://www.startribune.com/minnesota-bca-at-scene-of-shooting-involving-a-police-officer-in-brooklyn-center/600044821/), police were conducting a traffic stop when the driver attempted to pull away.

An officer fired toward the car, striking the driver who then drove into oncoming traffic.

Citizen will provide more details when they become available.
